battle":"英国","lifeSummary":"当James Armstrong于1101年出生在尼日利亚凱比阿雷瓦-丹迪法爾德时，他的父亲Allen Armstrong18岁，母亲Ella Knutson18岁。他于1124年与Margaret Mansfield在苏格兰结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1154年在他的家乡享年53岁。"},"hr":{"1101–1154":"1101.–1154.","1116–Male":"1116–preminuo","–Male":"preminuo","–Female":"preminula","1105–1124":"1105–1124.","1124–1152":"1124.–1152.","1083–Male":"1083–preminuo","1083–Female":"1083–preminula","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","1124":"1124.","1101":"1101.","1154":"1154.","1152":"1152.","1083":"1083","after 1124":"nakon 1124.","Falde,Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigerija","Falde, Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigerija","Scotland":"Scotland","England killed in battle":"England"},"cs":{"1101–1154":"1101–1154","1116–Male":"1116–Zesnulý","–Male":"Zesnulý","–Female":"Zesnulá","1105–1124":"1105–1124","1124–1152":"1124–1152","1083–Male":"1083–Zesnulý","1083–Female":"1083–Zesnulá","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1083":"1083","after 1124":"po 1124","Falde,Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigérie","Falde, Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigérie","Scotland":"Scotland","England killed in battle":"Anglie"},"da":{"1101–1154":"1101–1154","1116–Male":"1116–Afdød","–Male":"Afdød","–Female":"Afdød","1105–1124":"1105–1124","1124–1152":"1124–1152","1083–Male":"1083–Afdød","1083–Female":"1083–Afdød","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1083":"1083","after 1124":"efter 1124","Falde,Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria","Falde, Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria","Scotland":"Skotland","England killed in battle":"England"},"nl":{"1101–1154":"1101–1154","1116–Male":"1116–Overleden","–Male":"Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","1105–1124":"1105–1124","1124–1152":"1124–1152","1083–Male":"1083–Overleden","1083–Female":"1083–Overleden","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1083":"1083","after 1124":"na 1124","Falde,Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria","Falde, Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria","Scotland":"Schotland","England killed in battle":"England"},"en":{"1101–1154":"1101–1154","1116–Male":"1116–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1105–1124":"1105–1124","1124–1152":"1124–1152","1083–Male":"1083–Deceased","1083–Female":"1083–Deceased","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1083":"1083","after 1124":"after 1124","Falde,Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria","Falde, Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria","Scotland":"Scotland","England killed in battle":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Armstrong","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish (mainly Northumberland and the Scottish Borders): nickname from Middle English <i>arm</i> + <i>strang</i>, for someone who was ‘strong in the arm’.","Irish (Ulster): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Ó Labhradha Tréan</b> ‘strong O'Lavery’ or <b>Mac Thréinfhir</b>, literally ‘son of the strong man’.","History: This surname was brought to PA, NJ, and NH in the 18th century by several different families of northern Irish and northern English Protestants. One such was James Armstrong, who emigrated from Fermanagh to Cumberland County, PA, in 1745; another was John Armstrong (1720–95), who settled in Carlisle, PA, <i>c.</i> 1748."],"variants":[{"name":"Armstong","meanings":["Altered form of English   Armstrong  ."]}]},{"name":"James","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name borne in the New Testament by two of Christ's disciples, James son of Zebedee and James son of Alphaeus. This form comes from Late Latin <i>Iacomus</i>, a variant of <i>Iacobus</i>, Latin form of Greek <i>Iakobos</i>. This is the same name as Old Testament   Jacob   (Hebrew <i>Yaakov</i>), but for many centuries now they have been thought of in the English-speaking world as two distinct names. In Britain, <i>James</i> is a royal name that from the beginning of the 15th century onwards was associated particularly with the Scottish house of Stewart:  James I  of Scotland (  1394–1437 ; ruled  1424–37 ) was a patron of the arts and a noted poet, as well as an energetic ruler.  King James VI  of Scotland (  1566–1625 ; reigned  1567–1625 ) succeeded to the throne of England in  1603 . His grandson,  James II  of England (  1633–1701 ; reigned  1685–8 ) was a Roman Catholic, deposed in  1688  in favour of his Protestant daughter Mary and her husband William of Orange. From then on he, his son (also called James), and his grandson Charles (‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’) made various unsuccessful attempts to recover the English throne. Their supporters were known as Jacobites (from Latin <i>Iacobus</i>), and the name James became for a while particularly associated with Roman Catholicism on the one hand, and Highland opposition to the English government on the other. Nevertheless, it has since become one of the most perennially popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When James Armstrong was born in 1101, in Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeria, his father, Allen Armstrong, was 18 and his mother, Ella Knutson, was 18. He married Margaret Mansfield in 1124, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1154, in his hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1101–1154":"1101–1154","1116–Male":"1116–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1105–1124":"1105–1124","1124–1152":"1124–1152","1083–Male":"1083–Surnud","1083–Female":"1083–Surnud","1105":"1105","1116":"1116","1124":"1124","1101":"1101","1154":"1154","1152":"1152","1083":"1083","after 1124":"pärast 1124","Falde,Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeeria","Falde, Scotland":"Falde, Arewa-Dandi, Kebbi, Nigeeria","Scotland":"Scotland","England killed in battle":"England"},"fi":{